# PGConfig API

This page contains the PGConfig API documentation.

## Tuning Advisor [/tuning/get-config{?env_name,format,max_connections,pg_version,total_ram,show_doc}]

### /tuning/get-config [GET]

+ Parameters
    + env_name (enum[string],optional)
    
        Changes de environment
        
        + Default: `OLTP`
        + Members
            + `WEB`
            + `OLTP`
            + `DW`
            + `Mixed`
            + `Desktop`
    + format (enum[string],optional)

        Changes de default output
        
        + Default: `json`

        + Members
            + `json`
            + `conf`
            + `alter_system`
    + max_connections (integer,optional)

        Changes de max connection value
        
        + Default: `100`
    + pg_version (enum[float],optional)

        Changes de default PostgreSQL version
        
        + Default: `9.5`
        + Members
            + `9.1`
            + `9.2`
            + `9.3`
            + `9.4`
            + `9.5`
    + total_ram (string,optional)

        Changes the total memory avaliable to the PostgreSQL server
        
        + Default: `2GB`
    + show_doc (bool,optional)

        Show parameter documentation
        
        + Default: `false`


